    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Lord Neel has ordered you to make a new civilization on a planet and you have to design the terrain of the planet. The planet has <b>N</b> blocks of land. The first block is the godly block you cannot change its height. For the next N-1 blocks, you can cut them to any height you want. You want to maximize the sum of difference between the heights of adjacent blocks. Find the maximum sum of differences possible.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains the number of test cases <b>T</b>.\n\tEach testcase has two lines\n\t<ul>\n            <li>One integer <b>N</b> denoting number of bags.</li>\n\t    <li>N integers, first one is height of godly block and others are the difference of the height of the block and the godly block.</li>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Output one line for each testcase corresponding to the answer.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>6</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N(i)</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>9</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n1\n4\n6 6 6 6\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n30\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p>The godly block is of size 6. If we cut the blocks to heights 6 12 0 12, we get sum of differences as 30  i.e |6-12| + |12 - 0| + |0 - 12| </p>",
